author: Tom Brew
title: Small plane crash lands near Selma, Calif., Airport - @ABC30
text: Small plane crash lands near Selma Airport Plane crashes near an airport in Selma, Calif. (FAA) Saturday, August 01, 2015 01:49PM Officials from the Federal Aviation Administration are investigating what caused a small plane to crash-land near the Selma Airport Saturday.The single-engine plane, a Taylorcraft DCO-65, went down in a field near Huntsman and De Wolf Avenues.The FAA said one person suffered minor injuries.
